<item>
            <title>[LU-5098] /proc/sys/lnet/routes is stupid</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5098</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Presently /proc/sys/lnet/routers presents information about two more-or-less orthogonal concepts:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Whether this node is has lnet forwarding enabled (is itself acting as a router)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A list of networks that can be reached through peer nodes that are acting as routers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Examples:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Routing disabled
net      hops   state router
tcp         1      up 10.1.1.75@o2ib9
tcp1        1      up 10.1.1.75@o2ib9
tcp2        1    down 10.1.1.161@o2ib9
tcp3        1    down 10.1.1.162@o2ib9
tcp4        1      up 10.1.1.75@o2ib9
o2ib2       1      up 10.1.1.159@o2ib9
o2ib2       1      up 10.1.1.160@o2ib9
o2ib6       1      up 10.1.1.52@o2ib9
o2ib6       1      up 10.1.1.51@o2ib9
o2ib6       1      up 10.1.1.53@o2ib9
o2ib6       1      up 10.1.1.54@o2ib9
o2ib100     1      up 10.1.1.75@o2ib9
o2ib500     1      up 10.1.1.75@o2ib9
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Routing enabled
net      hops   state router
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first &quot;Routing &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;enabled|disabled&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; line should be not be in the routes file.  There should be a separate proc file for that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
